reviews.text: A very very relaxing cafe. Thanks to it's rather remote location, not many come here and you can enjoy a long day without any disturbances here. The only inconvenience is that the washroom is located a minute away from the cafe.

Since it is located in a remote area, therefore unlike other branches of Pacific Coffee, there is not a lot of customers.  You can relax in a quiet and comfortable environment to enjoy the delicious coffee and snack.

result.name: Jao Tsung-I Academy

reviews.text: A hidden treasure of Hong Kong's history. A great place to spend some leisurely hours visiting the exhibits and shops on the multi levelled escarpments.

A meaningful place that records the unique history of the place, a prison and a psychiatric ward.  Kids enjoy the exhibits.
15 minutes walk from the Mei Foo MTR station but taking taxi would be a better choice because the place can be hard to find if approaching on foot.
Very meaningful and historical heritage place to visit. Unfortunately, not many visitors due to its location at rather secluded  Hill top area.

A nice 1-1.5 hour walk around covering history of this heritage site on the hillside of Lai Chi Kwok. The facilities served many purposes in the over past 100 years as a trade hub, a transition camp for mainland migrant workers, a vaccination development center and an elderly care center. Offers nice view to the Lai Chi Kwok Bay area.

Nice environment, not far from MTR station. 
But not for my 4 yrs old kid

result.name: 饒宗頤文化館

reviews.text: 新舊文化交融👍🏻
😃好好玩
文化館本身不錯，對饒老先生的介紹亦很詳盡，地方清靜幽雅，很值得一去！但那餐廳就貴得過份，比一般酒店還要貴，一個人食一個full set 西餐最慳都要超過400元！本人認為以前由一些長者経營的銀杏館較為實際。
一入到去已經有嘢咬，跟住都冇心機行啦！下次等冬天先至去，希望冇嘢咬啦！
閒日去hea吓，城市中一綠洲，但遺憾是没公衆停車場
